  "rationale": "<p>Choice D is correct. Adding the corresponding sides of the two equations eliminates <span class=\"italic\">y</span> and yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x equals 6\"></span>, as shown.<p><span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"The equation one half y equals 4, added to the equation x minus one half y, equals 2, gives the equation x plus 0, equals 6\"></span></p><p>If (<span class=\"italic\">x</span>, <span class=\"italic\">y</span>) is a solution to the system, then (<span class=\"italic\">x</span>, <span class=\"italic\">y</span>) satisfies both equations in the system and any equation derived from them. Therefore, <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x equals 6\"></span>.</p><p>Choices A, B, and C are incorrect and may be the result of errors when solving the system.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n",
